llItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"ce8e8c93-7919-5160-9ad5-965fcd16658f","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"e05609c9-c42a-5eec-b055-39a296c3e2ea","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"e4f27b22-bcda-54f2-83f3-4ebf35f962ba","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"0ce2862f-cdca-57b0-9998-9bc40799914a","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"7e057656-6867-5510-95c7-019671326f4b","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"687c951d-457b-52b6-93f8-e38d5eafe6ed","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"f17589e6-56a0-535c-aa03-0856855943bb","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"2c583161-dd9d-5bf1-9fb1-a1395842cac9","slug":"prescribing-information","fullItemName":"Prescribing information"},"subChapters":[{"id":"36bfe1d9-452d-5471-b41b-062f272b2bad","slug":"contraindications-cautions","fullItemName":"Contraindications and cautions","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 75952a75-70ae-46c2-8523-a8c5015d9166 --><h3>Contraindications and cautions</h3><!-- end field 75952a75-70ae-46c2-8523-a8c5015d9166 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item c0014250-ea95-4fc6-9895-a8c5015d90ca --><!-- begin field 5bfd051a-bb48-40aa-8d07-a8c5015d9166 --><p><strong>The use of topical antifungal agents for treatment of fungal scalp infection is an off-label indication.</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Ketoconazole 2% shampoo </strong>is licensed for use in adults and young people aged 12 years and over.<ul><li>Advise the person to avoid contact with the eyes and mucous membranes during use.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Selenium sulfide 2.5% shampoo </strong>is licensed for use in adults and children aged 5 years and over.<ul><li>Advise the person to avoid use on broken or severely inflamed skin.</li><li>Advise that gold, silver, and other metallic jewellery should be removed before use, as discolouration may occur.</li><li>Advise that use should be avoided 48 hours before or after applying hair colouring, straightening, or waving preparations.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Clotrimazole 1% cream </strong>is licensed for use in children and adults.<ul><li>Advise the person to avoid contact with the eyes and mucous membranes during use.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Miconazole 2% cream </strong>is licensed for use in children and adults.<ul><li>Advise the person to avoid contact with the eyes and mucous membranes during use.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Econazole 1% cream </strong>is licensed for use in children and adults.<ul><li>Advise the person to avoid contact with the eyes and mucous membranes during use.</li></ul></li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/fungal-skin-infection-scalp/references/\">BNF for Children, 2017</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/fungal-skin-infection-scalp/references/\">BNF 75, 2018</a>] </p><!-- end field 5bfd051a-bb48-40aa-8d07-a8c5015d9166 --><!-- end item c0014250-ea95-4fc6-9895-a8c5015d90ca -->","subChapters":[]},{"id":"a096f1a4-c406-566d-aa87-a5a48110b603","slug":"adverse-effects","fullItemName":"Adverse effects","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 0f0b3706-a22e-45c8-99dc-a8c5015da0e4 --><h3>Adverse effects</h3><!-- end field 0f0b3706-a22e-45c8-99dc-a8c5015da0e4 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 719c3a01-da64-44f7-b464-a8c5015da04e --><!-- begin field 3dff9c43-bc15-4df1-bbad-a8c5015da0e4 --><ul><li><strong>Possible adverse effects with topical antifungals are uncommon</strong> and may include erythema, hypersensitivity reactions, itching, mild burning sensation, occasional local irritation.<ul><li>In addition, selenium sulfide 2.5% shampoo may rarely cause skin blistering, hair discoloration, or an increase in the amount of normal hair loss.</li></ul></li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/fungal-skin-infection-scalp/references/\">BNF for Children, 2017</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/fungal-skin-infection-scalp/references/\">BNF 75, 2018</a>] </p><!-- end field 3dff9c43-bc15-4df1-bbad-a8c5015da0e4 --><!-- end item 719c3a01-da64-44f7-b464-a8c5015da04e -->","subChapters":[]},{"id":"4a754351-aaf5-519b-818b-917eed808a49","slug":"drug-interactions","fullItemName":"Drug interactions","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field c94d3967-594d-40cb-87a7-a8c5015db025 --><h3>Drug interactions</h3><!-- end field c94d3967-594d-40cb-87a7-a8c5015db025 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 27a1cde5-068b-497a-bd19-a8c5015daf8f --><!-- begin field 6aa36548-91e3-4d58-bc73-a8c5015db025 --><ul><li>Topical ketoconazole shampoo — no drug interaction studies have been performed for ketoconazole shampoo, and there are no known significant drug interactions.</li><li>Topical selenium sulfide shampoo — should be very thoroughly rinsed from the hair before dyeing, tinting, or permanent waving the hair. It should not be applied for a period of 48 hours before or after any of these procedures.</li><li>Topical clotrimazole cream — there are no known significant drug interactions.</li><li>Topical miconazole and econazole cream — oral miconazole and econazole are known to interact with oral anticoagulants, but due to the limited systemic availability of topical preparations, clinically relevant drug interactions are rare. The manufacturer advises, however, that caution should be exercised and the anticoagulant effect should be monitored during concurrent use with an oral anticoagulant.</li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/fungal-skin-infection-scalp/references/\">ABPI, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/fungal-skin-infection-scalp/references/\">ABPI Medicines Compendium, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/fungal-skin-infection-scalp/references/\">ABPI, 2015a</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/fungal-skin-infection-scalp/references/\">ABPI, 2015b</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/fungal-skin-infection-scalp/references/\">ABPI, 2015c</a>]</p><!-- end field 6aa36548-91e3-4d58-bc73-a8c5015db025 --><!-- end item 27a1cde5-068b-497a-bd19-a8c5015daf8f -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}